CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 20, 1962, pg. 10 reads:" 'Y' Ranch hands In Big '62 Round-Up - Buff Circle Ranch - The 1962 membership enrollment of the "Y" has a Buff Circle Ranch, comprised of top Pittsburgh salesmen. Shown above are, left to right: James Burgette, YMCA branch executive; Erroll B. Davis, ranch boss; Jack Wright, president of the sales group, and Louis Boykins.  Standing: Al Malone, James Dyer, Kingsley Carey, Walter Jones, W.A. Arvin, Robert French, Buddy Malone and John Adams."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait, seated from left: James Burgette, Erroll B. Davis, Jack Wright, Louis Boykins; standing: Al Malone, James Dyer, Kingsley Carey, Walter Jones, W. A. Arvin, Robert French, Buddy Malone, and John Adams, gathered in Centre Avenue YMCA during 1962 membership campaign
